					<p>I agree, Textile is a cool thing. But why would you want this "SoftHack"? You state a wonderful point about Textile, the fact that it can create perfectly valid XHTML - and then you want a hack which ruins this? The "target"-attribute is not allowed in XHTML 1.0 Strict (if you want Transitional or Frameset, you could just as well use HTML4). Furthermore, such choices should be up to the user imho. And even if you'd like to "force" the user into a separate window, use unobtrusive Javascript at least. And place a visual pointer for people so they may catch up on the behaviour instead of being annoyed with new windows popping up all around.</p>
